NBA Home Win Prediction Project

Project Description:

This project uses Python to build a simple predictive model for NBA games. The goal is to predict whether the listed home team wins a game based on pregame information such as team Elo ratings, opponent Elo ratings, forecasted win probability, and season information.

This is a classification project because the response variable has two possible outcomes:

- `1`: the home team won
- `0`: the home team lost

Dataset:

The dataset used in this project is a cleaned NBA game dataset based on FiveThirtyEight's NBA Elo data.

The data file included in this repository is:

data/nba_home_2000_2015.csv
